  "prompt": "Why mobile phone is also know as cell phone?",
  "response": "A mobile phone is called a \"cell phone\" because of the cellular network technology it uses to communicate. Here's a more detailed explanation:\n\n1. Cellular Network Structure:\n- The geographical area is divided into smaller hexagonal regions called \"cells\"\n- Each cell has its own communications tower or base station\n- These cells are connected to form a network that covers a larger area\n\n2. How It Works:\n- When you move between cells during a call, the signal is automatically transferred from one cell tower to another\n- This seamless handoff allows continuous communication while moving\n- The phone \"hands off\" between cells without interrupting the call\n\n3. Origin of the Term:\n- The term \"cellular\" comes from the cellular network's structure\n- Each cell acts like a small unit or \"cell\" in the network\n- As you move, your phone connects to different cells\n\n4. Historical Context:\n- This technology was first developed by Bell Labs in the 1940s\n- Commercial cellular networks began in the 1980s\n- The term \"cell phone\" became popular during this period\n\nSo, a mobile phone is called a \"cell phone\" because it operates within a cellular network composed of interconnected cells, each with its own communication tower.",
